 and the Government of Flanders pays the other half. You thus receive a maximum allowance of 125 euros per school year.</p><p>In certain cases, you are entitled to an increased allowance.</p><ul><li>If you do not have a certificate of secondary education and you are following one of the training courses listed below, the Government of Flanders will pay the entire amount of the training voucher. You will then receive an increased maximum allowance of 250 euros:<ul><li>basic literacy</li><li>numeracy skills</li><li>ICT skills</li><li>Dutch for non-Dutch speakers</li><li>a training course that leads to a certificate of secondary education or level 4 vocational qualification</li><li>a shortage occupation training course.</li></ul></li></ul><ul><li>If you do not have a higher education diploma and you follow a training course that leads to a graduate or bachelor’s degree, you can purchase a training voucher to a maximum amount of 500 euros. You pay half of this and the Government of Flanders pays the other half. You will then receive an increased maximum allowance of 250 euros.</li></ul><p>If your level of education and the training course that you wish to follow combined entitle you to an increased allowance, this will be automatically allocated upon your application.</p>","nl-BE-x-generated-informal":"<p><strong>Per schooljaar </strong>kan je een <strong>opleidingscheque </strong>aankopen voor een bedrag (= nominale waarde) van <strong>maximaal 250 euro</strong>. Je betaalt daarvan de helft, de Vlaamse overheid betaalt de andere helft. Je krijgt dus een <strong>tegemoetkoming </strong>van <strong>maximaal 125 euro </strong>per schooljaar. </p><p>In bepaalde gevallen heb je recht op een <strong>verhoogde tegemoetkoming.</strong></p><ul><li><p>Als je <strong>geen diploma secundair onderwijs</strong> hebt en je volgt één van de <strong>onderstaande opleidingen</strong>, dan betaalt de Vlaamse overheid het volledige bedrag van de opleidingscheque. Je krijgt dan een <strong